<div class="list-group">
<div class="list-group-item">
Panchangam = Pancha (Five) + Anga (Elements)
</div><!--/.list-group-item -->
</div><!--/.list-group -->
<!-- -->
<div>
The Five Elements of Panchanga are
<ul>
<li>Vaara (Week)</li>
<li>Thithi (Day)</li>
<li>Nakshatra (Star)</li>
<li>Yoga</li>
<li>Karana</li>
</ul>
and this five elements come to know based on the position of Sun and Moon.
</div>
<div class="mtop15p">
Vedic Astrology suggests few benefits of knowing these 5 Panchang Elements on Daily Basis :
<ul>
<li><b>Vaara (Day of the Week) -</b>  helps one to enjoy <code data-toggle="tooltip" title="long life">longevity</code></li>
<li><b>Nakshatra (Star the Moon is in) -</b> helps one dissolve bad karmas</li>
<li><b>Tithi (Moon Phase) -</b> helps one enjoy <code data-toggle="tooltip" title="Extremely large or great">immense</code> wealth</li>
<li><b>Yoga -</b> helps one to keep deep <code data-toggle="tooltip" title="pain/harm">afflictions</code> away</li>
<li><b>Karana -</b> helps one to get their desires fulfilled.</li>
</ul>
</div>

